Example:
ExmapleQuestion:
Due to the high housing prices and prices in China's large cities, the cost of living is significantly higher than that of small and medium cities, especially for small towns, the cost of living in large cities is several times that of small towns. In this way, it is bound to limit the rural population Influx of large cities. Therefore, China's only reliance on the development of large cities to achieve urbanization is an unsustainable and difficult road.

Which of the following is the premise implicit in the above argument?

 Option:
A:There is no upper limit on the capacity of large cities to absorb the rural population.;
B:All towns are fully developed before they can be called urbanized.;
C:Large cities are far more attractive to the rural population than small and medium cities.;
D:To achieve urbanization, cities need to fully absorb the rural population.;


 Answer:[D]



Question:
Compared with small and medium-sized cities, especially small cities and towns, large cities have higher living costs, which inevitably limits the entry of rural population. Therefore, the development of large cities alone cannot actually achieve urbanization.

Which of the following is the conclusion must be assumed.

 Option:
A:Urbanization is the only way for China's development.;
B:Simple development of large cities is not conducive to the promotion of urbanization.;
C:To achieve urbanization, the city must fully absorb the rural population.;
D:The attractiveness of large cities to the rural population in the outside world is significantly lower than that of small and medium-sized cities.;

Example:
ExmapleQuestion:
China has entered an aging society. Aging means not only increasing the population's elderly burden factor, but also reducing the labor input. In the face of the indisputable fact of China's aging, delaying the retirement age can greatly reduce the total labor force. insufficient.

If the following are true, what weakens the above argument?

 Option:
A:China's stock of working-age labor is at its peak, and about 100 million people of working age are not employed.;
B:According to China's current aging rate, China's labor force will still be about 710 million by 2050.;
C:more than 30% of China's 12 million new jobs every year are not born to retirees.;
D:China's population over 60 years old reached 180 million in 2012, accounting for 24% of the global population over 60 years old.;


 Answer:[A]



Question:
Many netizens have doubts about the proposal to solve the pension gap problem by delaying the retirement age. They believe that leaving elderly people who should be retired in their positions will squeeze the employment space of young people and increase the difficulty of finding jobs for young people. The problem. Experts explained that the late retirees are both producers and consumers, and their consumption can create new jobs.

If the following statement is true, which one strongly questioned the expert's interpretation?

 Option:
A:Delaying the retirement age will be opposed by people working in private enterprises.;
B:Only by stimulating economic development can the unemployment rate be radically reduced.;
C:The pension gap stems from the unreasonable design of China's pension system.;
D:The expert's explanation is based on the unproven assumption that the spending power of working seniors is significantly higher than that of retired peers.;

Example:
ExmapleQuestion:
A certain meeting invited Zhang, Wang, Li, Zhao, Sun, and Zhou from a certain unit. However, due to work arrangements, six people cannot go at the same time. Among them: Zhang and Zhao Only one person can participate in the meeting; Li and Zhao can only have one person to participate in the meeting; at least one of Zhang and Wang can participate in the meeting; two of three are Zhang, Sun and Zhou. Attend the meeting; both Wang and Li either attend the meeting or neither; if Zhao does not attend the meeting, then Sun does not attend the meeting.

According to this arrangement, the last person who did not attend the meeting may be ().

 Option:
A:Zhang and Wang.;
B:Wang and Li.;
C:Lee and Zhao.;
D:Zhao and Sun.;


 Answer:[D]



Question:
There are 6 singers? F, G, L, K, H, M.3 piano accompaniment? X, Y, W. Each piano accompanimentist happened to accompany two of the singers. Known condition information is as follows? (1) If X is F accompaniment, then W is L accompaniment. (2) If X is not a G accompaniment, then Y is an M accompaniment. (3) X or Y is H accompaniment. (4) F and G do not share accompaniment; L and K do not share accompaniment; H and M do not share accompaniment.

It is impossible for Y to accompany the following pair of singers?

 Option:
A:G and H.;
B:L and H.;
C:F and L.;
D:F and M.;

Example:
ExmapleQuestion:
The Prime Minister of the United Kingdom, Churchill, said: "After winning the war and making history, he must be the person who explains and records history. " This is a good illustration of why he values historical writings. Although not many people in history can record History, the winning party can record history as they wish.

This text is intended to illustrate?

 Option:
A:Historical records may not be true.;
B:Introduction to Churchill's work.;
C:Churchill is a statesman and historian.;
D:The right to speak in historical records is very important.;


 Answer:[B]



Question:
The truth of history is not equal to the true history. Lu Xun said that "Historical Records" is "History's unique song, without rhyme". Good historical works must break through the rigid historical truth view, directly touch the souls of historical figures, and write the essence of history.

Which of the following statements is the assumption upon which the above argument relies?

 Option:
A:Good historical works not only faithfully report historical facts, but also vividly portray the souls of characters.;
B:Historical works that merely faithfully record historical facts are not good historical works.;
C:Among all historical works, only "Historical Records" is a good historical work.;
D:It is just a vivid depiction of the souls of historical figures. Works that do not report historical facts are not historical works.;

Example:
ExmapleQuestion:
To be a bestseller, a book must be readable or carefully packaged.

If the above assertion holds, which of the following must be true? ?

 Option:
A:Most people like readable bestsellers.;
B:Books that are not carefully packaged must not be bestsellers.;
C:Readable books must be bestsellers.;
D:Books that are not readable and carefully packaged are not necessarily bestsellers.;


 Answer:[D]



Question:
An editor is considering the issue of choosing the manuscript for the theoretical version of the newspaper. Six papers from E, F, G, J and K are available. Taking into account the content of the article, the layout of the newspaper and other factors. (1) If paper E is used, then paper F cannot be used but paper K must be used; (2) Paper G or paper H can only be used without paper J. (3) If you don't need thesis G, you don't need thesis K. (4) Essay E is a manuscript requested by a celebrity and cannot be used.

If the above items are true, which of the following items must be true?

 Option:
A:Paper E is used, but paper H is not used.;
B:Both articles G and H are used.;
C:No paper J, but paper K.;
D:Both G and J articles are unnecessary.;

Example:
ExmapleQuestion:
The way of thinking of modern science has undergone tremendous changes in the development of modern science, forming a new angle and new direction that is very different from modern science. It has shifted from mechanical thinking to system-oriented thinking. Holism, dynamics, complexity and contingency.

This passage mainly supports such an argument, that is?

 Option:
A:The way of thinking of modern science has undergone tremendous changes in the development of modern science.;
B:The thinking mode of modern science is obviously different from that of modern science.;
C:The dominant thinking of modern science changes from a mechanical perspective to a systematic perspective.;
D:Modern science is dominated by system view.;


 Answer:[C]



Question:
Philosopher? In the 18th century, a paper on motion is absolute asserted that the change of an object's position over time can be measured without reference to the position of any other object. However, a well-respected physicist claimed that this paper is incoherent. Since an incoherent paper cannot be regarded as a description of reality, movement cannot be absolute.

Which of the following methods or techniques of argument does the philosopher use in his argument?

 Option:
A:Use professional terminology to convince others.;
B:Rely on the authority of an expert to support a premise.;
C:It is reasonable to use experimental results to illustrate the mentioned changes in location.;
D:It is observed that something is a certain condition under experimental conditions, and it is also the case in any case when it is pushed out.;

Example:
ExmapleQuestion:
In recent days, continuous rainfall in the southern part of the country has caused many artificial fish ponds to be flooded. Therefore, several fish-farming experts have predicted the price trends of catfish and carp? Li Qiang said: Only when the price of catfish increases, carp prices will rise; Sun Zhen said: The price of at least one of catfish and carp will rise; Wang Gang said: only if the price of carp does not rise, the price of catfish will not rise; and if the price of catfish does not rise, the price of catfish will not rise.

If it turns out that all three experts' predictions are true, which of the following must be true?

 Option:
A:Catfish prices rise, carp prices do not rise.;
B:Catfish prices do not rise, carp prices rise.;
C:Both catfish and carp prices have risen.;
D:Prices of both catfish and carp have not risen.;


 Answer:[C]



Question:
A blogger declared? "My analysis of the future trend of housing prices has received more than 1,000 netizens' follow-up posts. I counted them, and 85% of the follow-up posts agree with my opinion. This shows Most people agree with me. ".

Which of the following can best question the blogger ’s conclusion?

 Option:
A:Although some people agree with his views, they do not agree with his analysis.;
B:The blogger's other articles with higher approval ratings later proved to be wrong.;
C:Some of the objections to the post are more fully justified.;
D:Most people who follow this blogger's article are their loyal fans.;

Example:
ExmapleQuestion:
Some geologists believe that if the average oil reserves per unit area in the unexplored area of the earth can be the same as the explored area, then the current correct estimate of the energy content of the underground unexploited will, therefore, multiply by 10,000 times From this, it can be concluded that global oil demand can be met for at least the next five centuries, even if such demand is increasing every year.

In order for the above argument to be true, which of the following must be assumed? ?

 Option:
A:The total area of unexplored areas on Earth is 10,000 times that of explored areas.;
B:For at least the next five centuries, the growth rate of the world's population will not exceed the growth rate of demand for oil.;
C:New technologies will make future exploration and extraction of oil more feasible than they are now.;
D:Petroleum stored in unexplored areas on Earth can be surveyed and extracted.;


 Answer:[D]



Question:
The raw material of cement is very cheap, like limestone and mud everywhere can be used as raw material of cement. However, the price of cement will be influenced by the price of oil, because it takes a lot of energy to convert raw materials from Pakistan to cement in high-temperature furnaces.

Based on the above conclusions, which of the following conclusions is most likely to be drawn?

 Option:
A:Petroleum is one of the raw materials contained in cement.;
B:Petroleum is the energy source of some high-temperature furnaces for making cement.;
C:The price of cement falls as the price of oil rises.;
D:The higher the price of cement, the higher the price of limestone.;

Example:
ExmapleQuestion:
Many nations in the world are facing the loss of their mother tongue's right to speak on the world stage, and have to rely on the West to make up their language, thus gradually weakening their own culture.

This passage can be used to prove which of the following points?

 Option:
A:The importance of protecting the mother tongue of the nation.;
B:Language is also divided into strong and weak.;
C:Reasons for the gradual weakening of national culture.;
D:We cannot adhere to the West in language.;


 Answer:[C]



Question:
In today's economic globalization, Western cultural classics and traditions are still alive and continuing. In the United States, the President takes the oath of office under the Bible, and elementary school students recite the oath of "a country under the protection of God" by pressing the chest every week. In China, elementary school students have long ceased reading the Bible, and no one has sworn in according to the Analects. China has become a country that has almost lost its cultural classics and traditions.

Which of the following statements is the assumption upon which the above argument relies?

 Option:
A:With the rapid advancement of science and technology, Western cultural classics and traditions are declining.;
B:Officials in Chinese history have never handed down the tradition of swearing on a classic.;
C:Primary school reading is a symbol of a country and nation maintaining cultural classics and traditions.;
D:The cultural classics and traditions of a country and nation have an irreplaceable role in science.;

Example:
ExmapleQuestion:
Often, the inability to change the living environment or the belief that someone is remotely controlling our actions somewhere will make us repulsive to learning; on the contrary, if we know that destiny is in our own hands, we will Work hard to learn and adapt. So when we have a real sense of responsibility for our actions, we learn faster.

This passage mainly supports such an argument?

 Option:
A:Changing the living environment is the most powerful motivation for learning.;
B:Responsibility for your own actions is an important factor affecting the speed of learning.;
C:Learning is an activity remotely controlled by others.;
D:Everyone must control their own destiny.;


 Answer:[B]



Question:
The important difference between a civilized man and a barbarian or other animals is to suppress the instinctive impulse through foresight. Only when a person does something is not driven by instinctive impulse, but because his reason tells him, At some point in the future he will benefit from it, and then there is real foresight. Cultivating the land is a far-sighted action, people work in the spring to eat food in winter.

Which of the following statements is the hypothesis that the above argument relies on?

 Option:
A:Is it possible to suppress the instinctive impulse by thinking deeply, this is the only difference between civilized people and barbarians or other animals.;
B:Actions such as squirrel burying chestnuts and arctic fox burying bird eggs are purely instinct-driven actions.;
C:The stronger the restraint of one's own instinct impulses, the greater the tolerance of the current pain, and therefore the higher the degree of civilization.;
D:People not only suppress their instinctive impulses through their foresight, but also suppress their instinct impulses through external laws, customs and religions.;

Example:
ExmapleQuestion:
There are four people: A. B, C, and D. If A is stocks, then B, C, and D are also stocks.

If the above assertion is true, then which of the following must also be true.

 Option:
A:If A does not have stocks, then B, C, and D have no stocks.;
B:If A does not have stocks, then at least one of B, C, and D have no stocks.;
C:If B, C, and D are all stocks, then A is also stocks.;
D:If Ding does not have stocks, then at least one of A and B does not have stocks.;


 Answer:[D]



Question:
A street comprehensive governance committee has 6 members? F, G, H, I, M and P. Each of these members must be a member of at least one of the three sub-committees under the Comprehensive Governance Committee. Each sub-committee is composed of 3 different members. The known information is as follows? one of the six members serves as a member of three subcommittees. F is not a member of the same subcommittee as G. H is not a member of the same subcommittee as I.

Which of the following statements must be true?

 Option:
A:One of F or G is a member of three subcommittees.;
B:One of H or I is a member of three subcommittees.;
C:P or M only serve on one subcommittee.;
D:One member happens to be a member of the two subcommittees.;

Example:
ExmapleQuestion:
The Little Swan Song and Dance Troupe have 45 young actors. About these 45 young actors, A. B and C have the following discussion: A said: "Some of these young actors are Beijingers. " B said: "Li Xinxin among the young actors is not Beijing, "C. said," Some of these little actors are not from Beijing. "In fact, only one sentence of the three is true.

Excuse me, which of the following options is true?

 Option:
A:5 young actors are not from Beijing.;
B:Some little actors are not from Beijing.;
C:Li Xinxin is not from Beijing.;
D:5 young actors are all from Beijing.;


 Answer:[D]



Question:
There are 6 singers? F, G, L, K, H, M.3 piano accompaniment? X, Y, W. Each piano accompanimentist happened to accompany two of the singers. Known condition information is as follows? (1) If X is F accompaniment, then W is L accompaniment. (2) If X is not a G accompaniment, then Y is an M accompaniment. (3) X or Y is H accompaniment. (4) F and G do not share accompaniment; L and K do not share accompaniment; H and M do not share accompaniment.

If X is an accompaniment to L and H, which of the following statements must be true?

 Option:
A:W is K accompaniment.;
B:Y is F accompaniment.;
C:G and K are accompanied by the same accompaniment.;
D:F and M are accompanied by the same accompaniment.;

Example:
ExmapleQuestion:
The reason is the most trusted tool when people need to make sound judgments to decide how to act in complex situations. Irrational tools such as hunch and habit are often used, but when it matters, or When success or failure depends on the point of judgment, it is undoubtedly the easiest way to succeed by resorting to rationality. We already have some reasonable methods that have been tested for a long time and can be used to determine which is appropriate and which is true. We also have a series of Established principles that can guide us to derive inferences from what is already known.

What does the text mean?

 Option:
A:The reason is the most reliable tool for people to make judgments.;
B:A set of methods already exists to help people make sound judgments.;
C:Irrational tools cannot be trusted when people need to make sound judgments.;
D:The judgment of complex situations based on rationality is not wrong.;


 Answer:[A]



Question:
Because the conclusion of quantum theory violates intuition, some scientists have different views on this theory. Although they try to strictly indicate that the assertion of quantum theory is inaccurate (that is, try to strictly falsify it), they find that the error lies in Usually within the acceptable statistical range. These results of quantum theory are different from those of competing theories, which makes it reasonable to accept quantum theory.

Which of the following principles is most helpful to show the rationality of the above reasoning?

 Option:
A:A theory should not be considered reasonable before it is tried to strictly falsify.;
B:Only if the assertion of a theory has not been falsified by experiments can this theory be accepted.;
C:If a scientific theory violates intuitive conclusions less than competing theories, then it should be accepted.;
D:If you try to strictly falsify a theory, but the theory has withstood all the tests, then you should accept it.;

Example:
ExmapleQuestion:
The ancient Greek playwright Euripides did not adhere to the rules of stylistic structure in his late writings as he did earlier. A recently discovered play by Euripides, in which the verses are as strict as his earlier plays, so the script must have been written by Euripides in the early days.

Which of the following is the assumption made above? ?

 Option:
A:Ancient playwrights tend to be more reluctant to break certain stereotypes in their later stages than in their early stages.;
B:Euripides did not write any script that mimicked the style of his earlier works late in his career.;
C:With the development of creation, Euripides is increasingly free from the conventions of its poetic structure.;
D:Late in his creative career, Euripides was the only playwright of his time struggling to break the rules of poetry.;


 Answer:[B]



Question:
Medieval Arabs have many ancient Greek manuscripts. When needed, they translated them into Arabic. Medieval Arab philosophers were very interested in Aristotle ’s Poetics, which was obviously not shared by Arab poets, because a poet who was interested in Poetics must want to read Homer ’s poems, Aristotle himself often quotes Homer's poems. However, Homer's poems were not translated into Arabic until now.

If the following statement is true, which one strongly supports the above argument?

 Option:
A:There are some medieval Arabic translators who own the manuscripts of Homer poems in ancient Greek.;
B:Aristotle's "On Poetry" is often quoted and commented on by modern Arabic poets.;
C:Aristotle's "Poetry Theory" is mostly related to drama. Medieval Arabs also wrote dramas and performed them.;
D:Medieval Arabic series of stories, such as "The Night of the Arabs", are very similar to some parts of Homer's epic.;

Example:
ExmapleQuestion:
A certain unit decided to send 2 women and 3 men to the provincial capital for training. After selection through various procedures, Which of the following candidates were finally identified: 3 women such as Lin Mou, Yang Mou, Tong Mou, and Chen Mou, He Mou, Wu Mou , 5 men such as Wang, Li, and also stipulated that at the same department, at most one person can be selected to participate in training. It is known that: Lin and Wang are from the same department, Wu and Chen are from the same department, and Wang is From the same place as Lee.

According to the above conditions, if Lin is selected, which of the following must be selected?

 Option:
A:Lee.;
B:Wang.;
C:Tong.;
D:Chen.;


 Answer:[A]



Question:
There are 7 candidates hired by Haier? F, G, H, I, W, X and Y. One of them needs to be assigned to the public relations department, three to the production department, and three to the sales department. The personnel allocation of these 7 employees must meet the following conditions? (1) H and Y must be allocated in the same department. (2) F and G cannot be allocated in the same department (3) If X is allocated in the sales department, W is allocated in the production department. (4) F must be allocated in the production department.

If which of the following statements is true, can the distribution of 7 employees be completely determined?

 Option:
A:F and W are assigned to the production department.;
B:G and Y are assigned to the sales department.;
C:I and W are assigned to the sales department.;
D:I and W are assigned to the production department.;

Example:
ExmapleQuestion:
In a certain restaurant, the dishes in the recipe belong to Sichuan cuisine, and the dishes ordered by Mr. Wang have Sichuan dishes.

Which of the following can be added to make the above argument true?

 Option:
A:The restaurant rules that if you order Sichuan food, you can not order Hunan food, but when you order Hunan food, you must order Sichuan food.;
B:The restaurant stipulates that when you order Hunan cuisine, you cannot order Sichuan cuisine and vice versa.;
C:Mr. Wang is from Sichuan and only likes Sichuan cuisine.;
D:Mr. Wang is from Hunan, he likes Hunan cuisine.;


 Answer:[B]



Question:
After all the cold dishes at the banquet at one table were served, there were 7 hot dishes. Among them, three Sichuan dishes? K, L, M? three Cantonese dishes? Q, N, P? one Shandong dish? X. Only one hot dish can be served at a time, and the order of serving must meet the following conditions? (1) Cannot serve Sichuan cuisine or Cantonese cuisine continuously. (2) Unless the second is on Q, P cannot be on before Q. (3) P must be on before X. (4) M must be on before K, and K must be on before N.

If the third is M, which of the following statements may be true?

 Option:
A:Fifth on X.;
B:First on Q.;
C:Sixth on L.;
D:Fourth on K.;

Example:
ExmapleQuestion:
If colleges and universities can hire a large number of graduates from first-class universities overseas, it will undoubtedly help to improve the quality of teaching and scientific research. Therefore, the employment of graduates who have obtained doctoral degrees from domestic universities will not help improve the quality of teaching and research.

Which of the following ____ items, if true, will constitute the most powerful questioning of the above views.

 Option:
A:Higher education institutions cannot fully recruit graduates who have obtained PhD degrees from top overseas universities.;
B:In many colleges and universities, a considerable number of teachers have graduated from domestic colleges and have no experience of studying abroad.;
C:Graduates who have obtained a PhD from top overseas universities are more willing to stay overseas for employment, even after returning to China, they tend to work in foreign companies.;
D:Graduates hired by higher education institutions to obtain doctoral degrees from top overseas universities are usually jointly trained by domestic universities and overseas universities, and they also have doctoral certificates issued by domestic universities.;


 Answer:[D]



Question:
Some college teachers have overseas doctorates, so some overseas doctors have a high level.

Which of the following can guarantee the correctness of the above statement?

 Option:
A:All college teachers have a very high level.;
B:Not all college teachers have a high level.;
C:Some college teachers have a very high level.;
D:All high-level teachers have overseas doctorate degrees.;

